1 About

This document is a quick view on the ancestry data generated in the COPDgene project by running LAMP.

Some questions of the interest include:

  • What is the total number of local ancestry segments?
    • Remember that the number of SNPs is around 500K.
    • The number of segments reported in (Parker et al. 2014) is 38,566.
  • How long are these segments?
  • By doing a PCA model
    • Is PC1 all about the vector of global ancestry?
    • Are the other PCs (2, 3, ) are meaningful?

Notes:

  • The current version of PCA is accomplished on a covariance matrix estimated only on the ancestry data in Chr 1.

2 Load pre-computed data

annot <- copdgene_annot_acs()
acsg <- copdgene_acs_global()

acsg <- mutate(acsg, 
  acs_gr = cut(acs_global, breaks = c(0, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9, 1)))

3 Global ancestry

4 Annotation for local ancestry

Fields in the annotation table:

  • acs: ID name of the ancestry segment
  • chr: Cromosome (1-22)
  • num_snps: the number of snps in a segment
  • num_ind_diff: the number of individuals that are different when comparing the current and the next ancestry segments
    • NA values mean that that segment was the last in Chromosome
  • length_bp: the length of segment measured in bp
  • length_cM: the length of segment measured in cM (converted from bp by simply dividing by 1M)

4.1 The number of ancestries

N Computation
154,042 Here
37,194 Here (> 10kbp)
38,566 (Parker et al. 2014)

The total number of snps (available in the output ancestry files by LAMP) is 608,917.
